# Large binary reference data (the SFD dust maps and sncosmo SED models) is
# stored as raw git blobs rather than Git LFS. The shared LFS bandwidth budget
# was exhausted, which blocked submodule checkouts in CI; every file here is
# under GitHub's 100 MB per-file limit, so plain git works. The trade-off is a
# larger clone.
#
# sncosmo/bandpasses/ and sncosmo/spectra/ are small ASCII transmission curves
# and reference spectra that also stay in normal git so they remain diff-able.
